messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hey, uh, my friend is having a seizure.
Where are you at?
I'm not sure what the address is. I don't live here.
Okay, can you describe their condition?
She was feeding her blood. She's sitting there a little bit.
You think she's coming to a little bit?
I think she's coming through a little bit.
Okay, and how old is she?
Uh, I think she's 20.
Is that her yelling in the background?
No, that's not her. That's a different person.
What's wrong with the other person?
The same thing that's gone through, they took some kind of drug.
They took some kind of pill? Okay. So it's a drug overdose, possibly?
I don't know. I think it's some kind of hallucinogen.
Okay. So you've got two people having problems?
Yeah, he won't stop yelling. I've been trying to get him to calm down.
So you've got a male and a female?
Yeah.
Okay, I can hear him. Are they both conscious?
Yeah, I think he just knows a little bit.
Is she responsive?
No.
She's breathing, but she's non-responsive?
Yeah.
Okay. I'm going to let you go because I'm going to have to get a deputy to come there too. Anything else happens? You call me back, okay?
Okay.
Alright, thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, I just called a few minutes ago. My friend who's had another seizure.
Okay, the female?
Yeah.
Okay. I do have an ambulance and some deputies en route to your location. Is she still breathing?
Yeah.
Okay, is blood still coming out of her mouth?
Every now and then just a little bit. Just a little drop like maybe she's bitten her cheek or something?
She's really hot?
Yeah, she's burning up.
Okay. I'll update the ambulance that's coming in. What about the male subject? Is he still yelling?
Yeah, he's kind of rolling around on the floor now, yelling.
